verses.verse: A Song of Ascents. Of David. O Jehovah, my heart is not proud, nor have my eyes been lofty; nor have I walked in great things, and not in things too wonderful for me.
If not I have set myself and have quieted my soul, like one weaned by its mother; my soul on me is as one weaned.
Let Israel hope in Jehovah, from now and till forever.
